==English==

===Etymology===
The term has arisen from the conflicts in the 20th century [[Balkans]].

===Alternative spellings===
*[[Balkanisation]]

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
# A geopolitical term to describe the [[fragment]]ation of a [[region]] into several small states that are often [[hostile]] or non-cooperative with each other.
# ''(colloquial)'': Any [[disintegration]] process, such as that of the Internet being divided into [[separate]] enclaves.

